properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 1 at 3:33AM PST until January 2 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts to 50 mph expected.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County South Coast. Strongest in the hills
and canyons.

* WHEN...From 2 PM this afternoon to noon PST Thursday. Strongest
tonight.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...While the strongest winds will be in the
hills and canyons, much of the South Coast will see sporadically
gusty winds.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO NOON PST THURSDAY
